sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dTomato
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: '''The dTomato protein is a fluorescent dimer protein that emits orange-red light when it is excited by green-yellow light. The excitation wavelengths and the emission wavelengths don't overlap as much as in other fluorescent proteins, which makes it preferable to use ??? especially in self‑made fluorometry tests.'''
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dianna Zeleskov
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: dTomato was derived from a monomeric mutant of the anthozoan coral RFP, DsRed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: dTomato
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The dTomato protein is a fluorescent dimer protein that emits orange-red light when it is excited by green-yellow light. It is preferable to use ??? especially in self-made fluorometry tests ??? because the excitation wavelengths and the emission wavelengths don't overlap as much as in other fluorescent proteins. The dTomato excitation peak is at 554 nm and 50% of it is at 510 nm. Also, its emission peak is at 581 nm and its 50% emission at 629 nm (Figure 1). Characterization has been made with the Anderson promoters BBa_J23101 and (construct BBa_K1688010) and BBa_J23110 (construct BBa_K1688011).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erik Gullberg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It was derived from a monomeric mutant of the anthozoan coral RFP, DsRed

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
